WEBVTT

00:00:05.427 --> 00:00:07.679
All traces of moe
culture have vanished

00:00:07.679 --> 00:00:09.473
from the streets
of Akihabara?!

00:00:09.473 --> 00:00:10.641
Please, Okarin! Wait for us!

00:00:10.641 --> 00:00:13.685
The hell, dude...?
I'm a hacker... not a hiker...

00:00:13.685 --> 00:00:16.396
Where'd Toranoana and
Animate go, huh...?!

00:00:16.396 --> 00:00:18.357
Where're Mandarake
and Gamers?!

00:00:18.357 --> 00:00:19.900
Now you're just being silly.

00:00:19.900 --> 00:00:22.569
You know we don't have
any of those around here.

00:00:22.569 --> 00:00:25.030
That's why I gotta go all the
way to Nakano for my doujin--

00:00:25.030 --> 00:00:25.989
Wait a sec...!

00:00:25.989 --> 00:00:28.992
You still work part-time
at Queen May's, don't you?!

00:00:28.992 --> 00:00:31.328
Huh? What's a Queen May's?

00:00:31.328 --> 00:00:33.497
Our favorite maid café!

00:00:36.541 --> 00:00:37.584
Impossible...

00:00:37.584 --> 00:00:38.835
It's quite alright, actually.

00:00:38.835 --> 00:00:41.338
Moe culture thrives here
mostly because of my influence.

00:00:41.338 --> 00:00:43.215
So it's a compliment.

00:00:43.215 --> 00:00:46.677
Did she send a D-mail
back in time to undo that?

00:00:46.677 --> 00:00:51.098
An entire city... rewritten by
a mere text message...!

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:59.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:02:39.539 --> 00:02:42.668
Hard to believe May Queen
Nyan-Nyan is no more...

00:02:42.668 --> 00:02:44.586
May Queen's a
type of potato, dude.

00:02:44.586 --> 00:02:47.255
Not feeling it as the
name of a maid café...

00:02:48.632 --> 00:02:51.343
What are you,
some tuber savant?

00:02:51.343 --> 00:02:53.512
Wait, if Queen May's
never existed...

00:02:53.512 --> 00:02:55.472
then how did we
first meet Faris?

00:02:55.472 --> 00:02:57.808
You can mock my random
bits of trivia all you want,

00:02:57.808 --> 00:02:59.851
but we wouldn't be
friends with Faris right now

00:02:59.851 --> 00:03:01.228
if it weren't for the spuds.

00:03:01.228 --> 00:03:02.354
Dare I even ask?

00:03:02.354 --> 00:03:03.563
How'd you forget...?!

00:03:03.563 --> 00:03:06.942
I was gonna kick some ass in the
Rai-Net tourney in Ikebukuro,

00:03:06.942 --> 00:03:09.820
but some bad potato ramen
was all "No--not yours,"

00:03:09.820 --> 00:03:11.822
and I had to skip it.

00:03:11.822 --> 00:03:12.572
Go on.

00:03:12.572 --> 00:03:15.367
So you and Mayuri filled
in for me against Faris...

00:03:15.367 --> 00:03:18.453
Got both of your asses kicked,
in case you forgot that...

00:03:18.453 --> 00:03:21.373
But the girls've been friends
ever since, so good times...

00:03:21.373 --> 00:03:25.127
Hell, a little food poisoning
was worth the scenery.

00:03:25.127 --> 00:03:26.837
Interesting...

00:03:26.837 --> 00:03:27.963
Check it out, Ruka...!

00:03:27.963 --> 00:03:29.131
It's a photo-book full

00:03:29.131 --> 00:03:31.174
of professional cosplay
I bought in Nakano!

00:03:31.174 --> 00:03:32.717
Oh wow...! They're so adorable!

00:03:32.717 --> 00:03:35.470
So even though the past has
been substantially altered,

00:03:35.470 --> 00:03:38.390
our relationships are
essentially the same...

00:03:38.390 --> 00:03:39.766
Yeah? Me, too!

00:03:39.766 --> 00:03:41.810
If only I could get you
to coo over schematics

00:03:41.810 --> 00:03:44.396
the way you do over cosplay.

00:03:44.396 --> 00:03:45.897
Oh...! Afternoon, Okabe!

00:03:45.897 --> 00:03:47.691
It's super-cute, don'tcha think?

00:03:47.691 --> 00:03:48.108
Whoa...!

00:03:48.108 --> 00:03:48.817
Huh...?

00:03:48.817 --> 00:03:50.569
Sedona...

00:03:50.569 --> 00:03:51.945
So much detail!

00:03:51.945 --> 00:03:54.197
And there's a
swimsuit version, too!

00:03:54.197 --> 00:03:55.699
I wish I could wear that...

00:03:55.699 --> 00:03:57.993
But I'm so not curvy
enough to pull it off well.

00:03:57.993 --> 00:03:58.869
Don't you worry!

00:03:58.869 --> 00:04:01.663
Small boobies
will have their day!

00:04:02.497 --> 00:04:04.291
Hey! We should all
take a field-trip

00:04:04.291 --> 00:04:06.251
to the beach some weekend!

00:04:06.251 --> 00:04:08.044
You gotta come, Kurisu!

00:04:08.044 --> 00:04:09.963
School swimsuits for the win...!

00:04:09.963 --> 00:04:12.716
I dunno... Us and
the perv brigade?

00:04:12.716 --> 00:04:13.633
Aww...

00:04:13.633 --> 00:04:16.136
Hey! I'm not
saying we can't go--

00:04:16.136 --> 00:04:17.721
if we make it a girls-only trip,

00:04:17.721 --> 00:04:20.432
then I'm totally down for
some beachside fun in the sun!

00:04:20.432 --> 00:04:23.518
Hahaha!
Abandon this charade, Christina!

00:04:23.518 --> 00:04:25.270
In truth, you
don't want us along

00:04:25.270 --> 00:04:27.147
because we might see
the unfortunate birthmark

00:04:27.147 --> 00:04:29.608
marring your
hindquarters... Right?

00:04:29.608 --> 00:04:31.777
What?! I don't have a birthmark!

00:04:31.777 --> 00:04:33.570
Besides... if this
outing to the beach

00:04:33.570 --> 00:04:36.907
were really girls-only, that
would leave Rukako high and dry.

00:04:36.907 --> 00:04:38.283
Huh...? How so?

00:04:38.283 --> 00:04:39.826
As I pointed out
the other day...

00:04:39.826 --> 00:04:42.787
Ruka is, shall we say,
of the masculine persuasion.

00:04:42.787 --> 00:04:43.997
Huh?

00:04:53.715 --> 00:04:55.425
What the hell's
wrong with you...?

00:04:55.425 --> 00:04:58.804
Calling her a boy is a
pretty shitty thing to do.

00:04:58.804 --> 00:05:02.140
It makes me sad when you
say mean stuff like that...

00:05:02.140 --> 00:05:04.226
Dude... Not cool.

00:05:06.520 --> 00:05:08.897
Wait, why're you crying...?!
Oh, honestly!

00:05:08.897 --> 00:05:11.650
You troglodyte...!
Apologize to Ruka right now!

00:05:11.650 --> 00:05:13.109
Why should I apologize

00:05:13.109 --> 00:05:14.402
for saying what is
clearly the truth?!

00:05:14.402 --> 00:05:16.112
No--it's fine!

00:05:16.112 --> 00:05:17.822
You shouldn't
have to apologize...

00:05:17.822 --> 00:05:20.033
If that's the way that
you think of me, so be it.

00:05:20.033 --> 00:05:21.284
Well naturally it is!

00:05:21.284 --> 00:05:22.035
What else am
I supposed to think?

00:05:22.035 --> 00:05:23.745
Put a sock in it,
you jackass!

00:05:23.745 --> 00:05:25.330
I should go! I'm sorry!

00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:26.748
No y'don't!

00:05:26.748 --> 00:05:27.833
This has gone on long enough...!

00:05:27.833 --> 00:05:30.210
If Ruka's really the
girl you say she is...

00:05:30.210 --> 00:05:33.922
then why does she have a--!

00:05:33.922 --> 00:05:36.967
Uh...What the hell?

00:05:36.967 --> 00:05:39.844
No, stop!... Please...! Okabe!

00:05:41.972 --> 00:05:46.268
Rukako... You're... a female...?

00:05:46.268 --> 00:05:51.147
That's what we've... been
saying... this whole damn time!

00:05:53.441 --> 00:05:56.611
You look thrashed.
Everything okay?

00:05:56.611 --> 00:05:58.655
A little torture. Nothing a
new pair of legs won't fix...

00:05:58.655 --> 00:06:02.325
Tortured...?! I bet it
was that Makise chick!

00:06:02.325 --> 00:06:06.496
Yeah... But I... got it all
cleared up... I think...?

00:06:06.496 --> 00:06:07.872
What did she
do to your legs?!

00:06:07.872 --> 00:06:10.417
Huh?! Sweet heavens
no--don't touch them!

00:06:10.417 --> 00:06:12.252
She compelled
me to sit stock still

00:06:12.252 --> 00:06:14.963
on my haunches
for a full hour...!

00:06:14.963 --> 00:06:18.883
Lesser men would have
broken... but not me.

00:06:18.883 --> 00:06:19.759
I dunno...

00:06:19.759 --> 00:06:22.512
That seems pretty darn
low on the torture-ometer.

00:06:22.512 --> 00:06:23.471
Is that so...?

00:06:23.471 --> 00:06:25.098
You sound alarmingly
like a woman

00:06:25.098 --> 00:06:26.766
who knows what
she's talking about.

00:06:26.766 --> 00:06:28.935
Let's just say that
I've done my time.

00:06:35.859 --> 00:06:38.820
This is absolutely perfect
weather to go biking.

00:06:38.820 --> 00:06:40.322
I suppose.

00:06:43.116 --> 00:06:45.952
Hey... you feel
like going for a ride?

00:06:51.917 --> 00:06:58.548
I did assume... you had,
a... second bike...!

00:07:00.133 --> 00:07:04.846
So... I didn't come to
Tokyo to work in a TV shop...

00:07:04.846 --> 00:07:06.222
I'm looking for my dad.

00:07:06.222 --> 00:07:09.434
Why is that...? Did he
run off or something?

00:07:09.434 --> 00:07:10.644
It's been years...

00:07:10.644 --> 00:07:13.271
I don't even remember
what he looks like.

00:07:13.271 --> 00:07:14.439
He's somewhere in the city

00:07:14.439 --> 00:07:16.399
but that's all
I really have to go on...

00:07:16.399 --> 00:07:18.318
It's not much of
a smoking gun...

00:07:18.318 --> 00:07:21.905
but I have an old pin of his.

00:07:21.905 --> 00:07:23.365
You might want to
think about dropping

00:07:23.365 --> 00:07:26.409
the part-time job
and focusing all on this.

00:07:26.409 --> 00:07:29.079
Look, I... can't tell
you why exactly...

00:07:29.079 --> 00:07:32.040
but I'm only gonna have
one last chance to see him.

00:07:32.040 --> 00:07:33.875
Huh?

00:07:33.875 --> 00:07:34.959
Short version?

00:07:34.959 --> 00:07:37.170
I think my dad's gonna
be somewhere tomorrow.

00:07:37.170 --> 00:07:39.756
But if I show up and
he doesn't, that's it...

00:07:39.756 --> 00:07:41.675
I gotta move on,
either way.

00:07:43.635 --> 00:07:46.054
There's a place I gotta
be getting to pretty soon...

00:07:46.054 --> 00:07:49.307
'Cause y'know...
I'm a busy girl.

00:07:49.307 --> 00:07:51.226
Hell, if I don't find
him in Tokyo...

00:07:51.226 --> 00:07:53.561
I might as well quit looking.

00:07:55.855 --> 00:08:00.360
You are ill at ease.
And I... find I can relate.

00:08:00.360 --> 00:08:02.028
However...!

00:08:02.028 --> 00:08:04.447
You just made the
serendipitous error

00:08:04.447 --> 00:08:09.744
of disclosing your tale of
paternal woe to a mad scientist!

00:08:09.744 --> 00:08:13.164
Henceforth! You are
Lab Member Double-0 Eight!

00:08:13.164 --> 00:08:16.084
Resign yourself to being
our newest guinea pig!

00:08:16.084 --> 00:08:17.877
What are you gonna do to me?

00:08:17.877 --> 00:08:19.796
Alter your past, of course...

00:08:19.796 --> 00:08:22.465
It's all part of
my master plan...

00:08:22.465 --> 00:08:24.509
Helping you is
just a side-effect...

00:08:24.509 --> 00:08:27.512
You will send a D-mail to
your father, understood?

00:08:27.512 --> 00:08:30.557
In it, you will tell him
not to leave--and presto...!

00:08:30.557 --> 00:08:32.851
Home he shall remain!

00:08:35.729 --> 00:08:37.689
You're a nice guy,
you know that?

00:08:37.689 --> 00:08:39.441
What?!

00:08:39.441 --> 00:08:40.650
Either way...

00:08:40.650 --> 00:08:44.154
I feel a little bit better
about this than I did earlier.

00:08:45.363 --> 00:08:47.282
Guess I should
get back to work...

00:08:47.282 --> 00:08:50.368
Thanks for being a pal, Okabe!

00:08:50.368 --> 00:08:52.370
Hey, listen, I want you to
promise me you'll come

00:08:52.370 --> 00:08:55.040
to the lab tomorrow whether
you meet your father or not...!

00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:58.460
If he's not there, we'll help
you... for science, of course!

00:09:01.087 --> 00:09:05.341
For all your world-dom talk...
you're just a big ol' softie!

00:09:14.017 --> 00:09:15.143
All right...

00:09:15.143 --> 00:09:16.644
I will now summarize

00:09:16.644 --> 00:09:19.981
the basics of Operation
Eldhrimnir in layman's terms.

00:09:19.981 --> 00:09:21.733
What's with the Norse mythology?

00:09:21.733 --> 00:09:23.818
If Suzuha locates her father,

00:09:23.818 --> 00:09:25.236
we'll have a farewell banquet...

00:09:25.236 --> 00:09:28.114
We'll have dinner if she doesn't
find her father, as well...

00:09:28.114 --> 00:09:31.868
But we'll present it as a
kind of consolation send-off...

00:09:31.868 --> 00:09:33.995
If so, the D-mail
will be dessert.

00:09:33.995 --> 00:09:36.206
Uh oh... Who's gonna
tell Daru the plan?

00:09:36.206 --> 00:09:37.874
He's off meeting
his online friends,

00:09:37.874 --> 00:09:39.375
or some such nonsense...

00:09:39.375 --> 00:09:41.211
But never fear,
I've got his number...!

00:09:41.211 --> 00:09:44.923
This is how you hook a Daru.

00:09:44.923 --> 00:09:47.258
I took the liberty of sending
him a little white lie.

00:09:47.258 --> 00:09:49.636
Wait, are you bribing
him with food or Faris...?

00:09:49.636 --> 00:09:51.596
Either way,
that'll probably work.

00:09:51.596 --> 00:09:54.891
Huh...? But Faris told me
she couldn't be here tonight.

00:09:54.891 --> 00:09:56.601
Which I'm willing
to look beyond,

00:09:56.601 --> 00:09:58.895
since she's never
met Suzuha, but our

00:09:58.895 --> 00:10:01.731
resident hack's attendance
is decidedly mandatory.

00:10:01.731 --> 00:10:03.274
Um, actually...

00:10:03.274 --> 00:10:07.195
I've never met her, either.
Is it okay that I'm coming?

00:10:07.195 --> 00:10:08.238
But of course...!

00:10:08.238 --> 00:10:11.491
You ladies can do the
shopping for our little soiree.

00:10:11.491 --> 00:10:12.700
While you...?

00:10:12.700 --> 00:10:14.661
While I tail the
scrappy part-timer

00:10:14.661 --> 00:10:16.496
to see if her errant
parent "pops" up.

00:10:16.496 --> 00:10:17.372
Aw, come on...

00:10:17.372 --> 00:10:20.500
Don't go spying on their
father-daughter bonding time.

00:10:20.500 --> 00:10:21.501
Yeah, Okarin...!

00:10:21.501 --> 00:10:23.920
Why don't you just come on
our shopping trip with us!

00:10:23.920 --> 00:10:24.796
Following Suzuha is my--

00:10:24.796 --> 00:10:26.840
It's not gonna
happen, so drop it!

00:10:26.840 --> 00:10:30.426
Where does my assistant get
off telling me what to do...?!

00:10:30.426 --> 00:10:32.011
You remember earlier, right...?

00:10:32.011 --> 00:10:34.180
How 'bout three hours?

00:10:34.180 --> 00:10:36.057
All right...! Shopping it is!

00:10:36.057 --> 00:10:37.851
So shall we be off...?!

00:10:50.530 --> 00:10:52.782
Is something the
matter, Okarin?

00:10:52.782 --> 00:10:54.325
It's nothing...

00:11:01.374 --> 00:11:02.750
What in the...?

00:11:11.885 --> 00:11:14.721
Do you think we should
go with the mild curry...?

00:11:14.721 --> 00:11:16.264
Oh but, hot is so good.

00:11:16.264 --> 00:11:18.266
Which do you
think she'll like?

00:11:18.266 --> 00:11:21.311
Whatever is fine...
Let's go with the hot one.

00:11:21.311 --> 00:11:25.481
Hmm... Good idea! 'Cause
Suzuha's a pretty spicy girl!

00:11:25.481 --> 00:11:28.401
I betcha she can't even
taste the mild stuff!

00:11:28.401 --> 00:11:32.572
Okie-doke...
Next stop, the meat aisle!

00:11:32.572 --> 00:11:33.197
Wow!

00:11:33.197 --> 00:11:36.784
Lookit these prices--they're
sure proud of their stuff!

00:11:38.369 --> 00:11:40.079
Hey, Okarin...

00:11:40.079 --> 00:11:41.831
You've been so
quiet all night...

00:11:41.831 --> 00:11:44.417
I keep waiting for you
to say something like...

00:11:44.417 --> 00:11:46.336
"Looks like the Organization's
been messing around

00:11:46.336 --> 00:11:48.004
with the price
of local meat...!

00:11:48.004 --> 00:11:50.673
Launching Operation
Half-Off Sales Event!"...

00:11:50.673 --> 00:11:52.383
Or something like that.

00:11:56.054 --> 00:12:00.141
"Operation Half-Off Sales
Event" lacks in Nordic flare.

00:12:00.141 --> 00:12:02.602
It's me... They've
sabotaged the beef supply...

00:12:02.602 --> 00:12:04.771
Operation Audumbla
is still viable,

00:12:04.771 --> 00:12:06.648
albeit at a greater cost.

00:12:06.648 --> 00:12:09.442
Unlock additional culinary
funding on the double.

00:12:09.442 --> 00:12:12.570
Huh? Look...!
First star of the night!

00:12:13.905 --> 00:12:15.907
Oh that's Venus, actually.

00:12:18.743 --> 00:12:20.036
Hey, Okarin.

00:12:21.371 --> 00:12:24.374
Remember back when
we were little kids...

00:12:24.374 --> 00:12:26.751
and you had that
really bad fever?

00:12:26.751 --> 00:12:29.462
Yeah... Right when everyone
was losing their head

00:12:29.462 --> 00:12:32.048
over the whole Y2K thing.

00:12:32.048 --> 00:12:33.049
I was scared...

00:12:33.049 --> 00:12:35.009
You looked so sick and frail,

00:12:35.009 --> 00:12:36.928
I thought you were
gonna just fade away...

00:12:36.928 --> 00:12:39.806
I didn't want you to die.

00:12:39.806 --> 00:12:43.601
So I looked up at the
stars, and said a prayer.

00:12:43.601 --> 00:12:48.606
And right then... one went
shooting past right above me.

00:12:48.606 --> 00:12:50.441
So, as it went I said...

00:12:50.441 --> 00:12:54.487
"Don't take my Okarin!"... I
said it three times in a row...

00:12:54.487 --> 00:12:56.239
And the very next morning...

00:12:56.239 --> 00:12:59.784
your fever had broken and you
said you were feeling better!

00:12:59.784 --> 00:13:00.743
I don't mean to brag,

00:13:00.743 --> 00:13:04.497
but I kinda saved
your life, y'know.

00:13:04.497 --> 00:13:06.207
Sorry, but... you didn't...

00:13:06.207 --> 00:13:09.836
My surviving that fever was
the decision of Stein's Gate.

00:13:09.836 --> 00:13:13.047
Yeah...? Aw... That's no fun.

00:13:13.047 --> 00:13:14.340
I'm afraid so.

00:13:14.340 --> 00:13:19.012
Okay... Hey, remember
when you first got sick,

00:13:19.012 --> 00:13:22.765
how you fell down?
Remember what you said?

00:13:22.765 --> 00:13:23.850
You said you were dizzy,

00:13:23.850 --> 00:13:25.685
and that the
world felt all wiggly...

00:13:25.685 --> 00:13:28.563
Like you'd been zapped
by lightning, you told me...

00:13:28.563 --> 00:13:31.441
Like things didn't
make sense anymore.

00:13:31.441 --> 00:13:33.026
When we were back at Faris's...?

00:13:33.026 --> 00:13:36.779
Your face reminded
me of then.

00:13:36.779 --> 00:13:38.906
Sick in bed with that fever...

00:13:38.906 --> 00:13:41.284
I'd forgotten how that felt...

00:13:41.284 --> 00:13:45.705
It's the same way I feel
when I shift world-lines...

00:13:45.705 --> 00:13:48.833
I wonder... was
that bout of illness...

00:13:48.833 --> 00:13:52.086
the emergence of my
Reading Steiner ability...?

00:13:56.049 --> 00:13:57.550
Hey!

00:13:57.550 --> 00:13:59.093
Hey, you two!

00:13:59.093 --> 00:14:01.804
Huh...? What's that
odor assailing my nose?

00:14:01.804 --> 00:14:05.433
Oh, that? Kurisu decided to
make an apple pie for us...

00:14:05.433 --> 00:14:06.934
That stench is dessert?!

00:14:06.934 --> 00:14:08.770
I'd love to help...
you have a job for me?

00:14:08.770 --> 00:14:10.897
Sure! Why don't you
boil some eggs for me.

00:14:10.897 --> 00:14:12.356
Okay!

00:14:12.356 --> 00:14:13.608
Let's see... Ooh!

00:14:13.608 --> 00:14:15.526
I'll just pop 'em
into the Phone Wave!

00:14:16.819 --> 00:14:19.781
No, Mayuri--don't!
They'll explode in there!

00:14:20.406 --> 00:14:21.908
I can take care of it!

00:14:21.908 --> 00:14:22.950
Aww...

00:14:22.950 --> 00:14:25.036
You can chop the
mushrooms instead, yeah?

00:14:25.036 --> 00:14:26.370
Yaaaay!

00:14:26.370 --> 00:14:27.163
Wait a second...!

00:14:27.163 --> 00:14:30.166
What manner of Stygian dessert
are you trying to foist upon us?

00:14:30.166 --> 00:14:32.043
They're for the salad, genius.

00:14:32.043 --> 00:14:34.295
I defy you to find
me a single world-line

00:14:34.295 --> 00:14:35.588
in which egg and mushroom
salad goes with apple pie!

00:14:35.588 --> 00:14:37.423
Chop...! Chop...! Chop!

00:14:37.423 --> 00:14:39.425
I'm calling a moratorium
on the "chop chop chop!"

00:14:39.425 --> 00:14:41.135
Outta the way!

00:14:43.888 --> 00:14:45.139
Woe betide me...

00:14:45.139 --> 00:14:48.226
All the women have turned
into evil kitchen ghouls...

00:14:48.226 --> 00:14:51.354
If I don't call you back
in an hour's time, please...

00:14:51.354 --> 00:14:52.980
tell my parents
that I loved them...

00:14:52.980 --> 00:14:55.233
right up until
the bitter... end.

00:14:55.233 --> 00:14:58.945
'Scuse me, Okabe. Is there
a rice cooker in here?

00:14:58.945 --> 00:15:02.490
Heeeere's Daru...!
Wait a sec, where's Faris?

00:15:02.490 --> 00:15:04.992
Sorry... She can't make
it to our dinner tonight...

00:15:04.992 --> 00:15:07.703
looks like someone pulled a
fast one on you--guess who.

00:15:07.703 --> 00:15:10.373
What...?! Son-of-a...!
Man, you suck!

00:15:10.373 --> 00:15:12.708
Y'know, truth is a very
subjective phenomenon.

00:15:12.708 --> 00:15:14.127
Fat load of good that does me!

00:15:14.127 --> 00:15:16.963
I skipped my time-travel
meet-up for this!

00:15:16.963 --> 00:15:18.339
Time-travel meet-up?

00:15:18.339 --> 00:15:19.090
Don't judge.

00:15:19.090 --> 00:15:21.384
It's just a bunch of posters
from a sci-fi forum

00:15:21.384 --> 00:15:22.635
I moderate sometimes...

00:15:22.635 --> 00:15:25.388
We had a writer coming
as a guest tonight, too!

00:15:25.388 --> 00:15:28.516
This little kit is so cute!
What do you keep in here?

00:15:28.516 --> 00:15:30.726
I wouldn't go
touching that, Ruka!

00:15:30.726 --> 00:15:33.062
It's Future Gadget
numero four: Moad Snake!

00:15:33.062 --> 00:15:33.938
Is that a Claymore?!

00:15:33.938 --> 00:15:35.523
No, no, it's merely a mock-up...

00:15:35.523 --> 00:15:37.108
In actuality, it's a humidifier.

00:15:37.108 --> 00:15:38.067
Aha! Here we go!

00:15:38.067 --> 00:15:39.861
No--don't pull that!

00:15:50.746 --> 00:15:52.832
I'm so sorry, you guys...

00:15:53.457 --> 00:15:54.417
What's done is done.

00:15:54.417 --> 00:15:57.170
Just watch what you touch
from now on, all right?

00:15:57.170 --> 00:16:00.339
Hey... This might
help with the clean-up.

00:16:00.339 --> 00:16:03.217
A vacuum? Yeah, good thinking.

00:16:03.217 --> 00:16:04.051
Guess again...!

00:16:04.051 --> 00:16:05.720
It's Future Gadget
number three...!

00:16:05.720 --> 00:16:07.597
Or is it the second one?

00:16:07.597 --> 00:16:09.765
Number Five. A.K.A.

00:16:09.765 --> 00:16:13.561
"'I've Connected Yet Another
Trifling Thing,' a la Goemon."

00:16:13.561 --> 00:16:16.606
A.K.A. a hair dryer
that uses the heat output

00:16:16.606 --> 00:16:19.817
of a vacuum cleaner...
Here, gimme.

00:16:19.817 --> 00:16:20.735
Hold on!

00:16:20.735 --> 00:16:22.195
You have to
unplug everything else

00:16:22.195 --> 00:16:23.821
before you use it,
otherwise the--!

00:16:25.031 --> 00:16:26.157
...breaker will trip.

00:16:26.157 --> 00:16:29.452
Yeah... Anybody know
where the flashlight is?

00:16:29.452 --> 00:16:31.996
Um... is this it...?

00:16:31.996 --> 00:16:35.249
Uh... no... That's a cucumber.

00:16:35.249 --> 00:16:36.626
So... where's the fuse-box...?

00:16:36.626 --> 00:16:37.418
What's with that giggle, Mayuri?

00:16:37.418 --> 00:16:41.631
You're just going to
trip over something!

00:16:41.631 --> 00:16:42.882
Told you so.

00:16:42.882 --> 00:16:44.759
Oww...

00:16:44.759 --> 00:16:46.219
It's by the front door.

00:16:46.219 --> 00:16:47.970
Cool. Thanks.

00:16:49.180 --> 00:16:50.681
You okay?

00:16:56.229 --> 00:16:57.438
What's so funny?

00:16:57.438 --> 00:17:00.566
Sorry 'bout that...
It's just...

00:17:00.566 --> 00:17:01.943
Hmm?

00:17:01.943 --> 00:17:04.946
I thought of the lab
I work at back in America...

00:17:04.946 --> 00:17:06.530
It's top-notch, y'know?

00:17:06.530 --> 00:17:09.659
We're talking wall
to wall geniuses...

00:17:09.659 --> 00:17:13.162
But they're all so... cold...

00:17:13.162 --> 00:17:17.250
Scientifically, it blows this
place out of the water, but...

00:17:17.250 --> 00:17:20.211
I feel at home here.

00:17:20.211 --> 00:17:20.628
Hey!

00:17:20.628 --> 00:17:23.172
Don't go thinking that was
a compliment or anything...!

00:17:23.172 --> 00:17:25.716
I was just comparing and
contrasting the labs...

00:17:25.716 --> 00:17:28.010
That's all...

00:17:28.010 --> 00:17:31.180
I made this place because
I couldn't invent friends.

00:17:35.434 --> 00:17:41.357
It worked... I mean...
I'm still here, aren't I?

00:17:41.357 --> 00:17:42.608
And you know earlier...

00:17:42.608 --> 00:17:45.569
when you said you cherish
our friendship, it...

00:17:45.569 --> 00:17:50.741
well... it made me
happy... Like, a lot.

00:17:54.745 --> 00:17:56.998
Did you fall on your head?

00:17:56.998 --> 00:17:58.124
Wait, what...?!

00:17:58.124 --> 00:18:01.043
I try to say something nice,
and that's your reply...?!

00:18:01.043 --> 00:18:03.170
You're such a bastard!

00:18:14.849 --> 00:18:17.101
Suzuha sure is late, huh.

00:18:17.101 --> 00:18:19.395
I hope that means
she found her dad.

00:18:19.395 --> 00:18:20.688
Sure, I bet
they're catching up

00:18:20.688 --> 00:18:22.857
on father/daughter stuff
and they lost track of time.

00:18:22.857 --> 00:18:25.860
I made it very clear she was to
report to the lab either way...

00:18:25.860 --> 00:18:29.989
But I guess my instructions
were all for nothing.

00:18:29.989 --> 00:18:33.159
She isn't coming.
Let's call it a night.

00:18:47.381 --> 00:18:49.216
Why, that little...!

00:18:56.807 --> 00:18:59.101
So she's going to
slink off into the night,

00:18:59.101 --> 00:19:00.853
fatherless and alone...?

00:19:00.853 --> 00:19:04.649
Not on my watch. Hououin
Kyouma cannot abide this!

00:19:09.737 --> 00:19:10.613
Dammit!

00:19:10.613 --> 00:19:13.616
Where could she be?!

00:19:13.616 --> 00:19:14.909
Of course...

00:19:14.909 --> 00:19:16.660
I'll send a D-mail
instructing myself

00:19:16.660 --> 00:19:22.833
to tail Suzuha this afternoon
at all costs...! But...

00:19:22.833 --> 00:19:25.252
After everything
that's transpired...

00:19:25.252 --> 00:19:28.089
dare I alter the
past any further...?

00:19:28.089 --> 00:19:31.092
You're a nice guy,
you know that?

00:19:31.092 --> 00:19:32.259
Either way...

00:19:32.259 --> 00:19:35.554
I feel a little bit better
about this than I did earlier.

00:19:37.014 --> 00:19:38.849
I'm no thumb
twiddling milquetoast

00:19:38.849 --> 00:19:41.894
trembling in his lab coat...
I am Hououin Kyouma...

00:19:41.894 --> 00:19:44.939
I look into the
abyss with nary a fear!

00:19:59.328 --> 00:20:01.372
"Ignore assistant..."

00:20:02.581 --> 00:20:04.834
"...tail Suzuha!"

00:20:24.395 --> 00:20:26.397
Whassup.

00:20:26.397 --> 00:20:28.482
It's good to see
you're so hard at work...

00:20:28.482 --> 00:20:29.817
Late night, eh?

00:20:29.817 --> 00:20:32.319
No kidding--that party really
took on a life of its own!

00:20:32.319 --> 00:20:35.906
I'm running on fumes today...

00:20:35.906 --> 00:20:37.366
Humor me, if you would...

00:20:37.366 --> 00:20:40.286
We threw a consolation
dinner for you last night,

00:20:40.286 --> 00:20:43.622
one at which you served
as our test subject.

00:20:43.622 --> 00:20:45.499
Did we not?

00:20:45.499 --> 00:20:48.127
Yeah, but we never got
around to the guinea pig part,

00:20:48.127 --> 00:20:51.380
'cause I don't have
my dad's contact info.

00:20:51.380 --> 00:20:54.300
There's a detail
I'm kind of fuzzy on...

00:20:54.300 --> 00:20:57.928
Refresh my memory as to how you
ended up at the lab last night?

00:20:57.928 --> 00:20:59.805
Huh...? What were
you drinking...?

00:20:59.805 --> 00:21:03.058
Sounds like somebody
needs to lay off the sauce.

00:21:03.058 --> 00:21:05.436
Please, just indulge
me for a moment.

00:21:05.436 --> 00:21:06.520
Yeah, okay...

00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:09.607
I was just leaving the time-
travel forum meet-up when you--

00:21:09.607 --> 00:21:12.485
Uh... Time-travel
forum meet-up...?!

00:21:12.485 --> 00:21:14.278
When you told me your father
might show up somewhere,

00:21:14.278 --> 00:21:15.905
is that what you meant?!

00:21:15.905 --> 00:21:17.448
Yup. On the message boards,

00:21:17.448 --> 00:21:19.909
he posts under
the user ID Titor.

00:21:19.909 --> 00:21:21.535
Wait... John Titor?!

00:21:21.535 --> 00:21:25.039
Nuh uh, sorry.
Barrel... It's Barrel Titor.

00:21:25.039 --> 00:21:27.166
I told you at
the party, remember?

00:21:27.166 --> 00:21:29.376
You recorded me
saying it and everything.

00:21:30.961 --> 00:21:34.924
Oh man...! Last night
was so much fun!

00:21:34.924 --> 00:21:36.967
Course, it would've been
better without you-know-who...

00:21:36.967 --> 00:21:38.594
That pie of hers almost made it

00:21:38.594 --> 00:21:42.014
a farewell party
for everyone...!

00:21:42.014 --> 00:21:43.307
Ruka's curry, though...

00:21:43.307 --> 00:21:46.519
now that was some tasty stuff!

00:21:46.519 --> 00:21:49.563
I really do dig your lab...
Seriously cool!

00:21:49.563 --> 00:21:53.025
You all get along, and
you're always having fun.

00:21:53.025 --> 00:21:56.946
First time in my whole life
I felt like I really fit in.

00:21:56.946 --> 00:21:59.323
Come on up whenever you want.

00:21:59.323 --> 00:22:00.908
Surely I needn't remind you...

00:22:00.908 --> 00:22:03.410
You are a member of the lab now.

00:22:03.410 --> 00:22:05.746
Yeah. Maybe I'll stick around...

00:22:05.746 --> 00:22:08.582
Look for dear ol'
Dad a little bit more...

00:22:09.305 --> 00:23:09.156
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

